comments.message: This change requires the fix from FWINT-1078.

qti_signer:

2) SDX55 test (EM91xx):
sdx55_signer:

qti_signer:

3) NVU creation support with new qti_signer (EM91xx/WP77xx):
See logs in JIRA ticket: OEMPRI-24086

I expect em92 (x65c) will use the same process as x55c, is it correct? 

even through we only have devkit pri for em92, I assume we can use the same process as x55c which build carrier pri build with different folder

Based on discussion, shall we also revert this back? To the following:

if pri_type == "Carrier":

when we work on the em91, we have to use different folder for each carrier pri due to EFS folders checkout from svn.  For other products, all carrier pris can be handled within one simple folder.

So if it is OK, then we can use the same way (generate each sub-folder to each carrier pri) for legacy products.

I think this is a requirement for all products which use the qti_signer, as all of the signed files are named the same way (multifile.bin.signed.cwe and carrierpkg.bin.signed.cwe) and will need to be saved in their respective folders, i.e. temp_GENERIC/multifile.bin.signed.cwe
agreed,  then go ahead to fix the line #757
I expect these codes will be needed as well for em92

will need to delete temp_pri folder if it has been exist.  This will be present when last sign task fail

seems all the pri automation scripts use the following way to call subprocess which is more safe for subprocess calling

--------
   process = subprocess.Popen(cmd, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT)
   process.wait()
Better this line unchanged as we define the None default setting at line90
not need this line, see comment on line 743-748

sorry, seems these lines did not work on my local test.  WE have to switch back to your original codes which can work.

 proc = subprocess.Popen(cmd)
            (out, err) = proc.communicate()
            if proc.returncode != 0:

when sign fail, we will need to cleanup the output folder. Refer to the original codes which have these cleanup steps
----------
    proc = subprocess.Popen(cmd)
    (out, err) = proc.communicate()
    if proc.returncode != 0:
        variableClass.logger.error(err)
        printerrormsg("Unable to generate sign file. Error code: " + str(proc.returncode))
        # Cleanup Signing folder
        shutil.rmtree(outputPath, onerror=onerror)
        sys.exit(ERROR_GENERATE_SIGN_PACKAGE)
----------
Just curious if this fix is the same one mentioned in OEMPRI-17210?

hmm, in general, this is different issues .  This is just to clean the folder once the sign fails.  OEMPRI-17210 is to clean the output folder before we start a PRI build.  OENPRI-17120 fix will be useful when user use the same output folder for different PRI build and forgot the cleanup the output folder.

It will be nice to have both fix, but seems to me OEMPRI-17120 can cover this sign failure cleanup as well.
